            <scopecontent id="aspace_e27f3fb99f45ba4f50cb24c8184d0aed">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>This small collection, purchased by Yale University in 1941, consists of letters written to Hugh and William Thompson Peters from their father, John Thompson Peters, other family members, and others, and of manuscript and printed poems written by Hugh Peters. The latter are mounted in a catalogue of the library of Ithiel Town, father-in-law of William T. Peters. The papers in this collection are arranged by family member.</p>
            </scopecontent>
